<div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Welcome to {{title}} API</h1>
    <p class="text-xl mb-8">JSProdigy API is a powerful and easy-to-use API that allows you to manage user profiles, courses, and doubts.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Getting Started</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">To get started with JSProdigy API, follow these simple steps:</p>
    <ol class="list-decimal pl-8 mb-8">
        <li>Familiarize yourself with the API documentation below.</li>
        <li>Make HTTP requests to the API endpoints using your preferred programming language or tool.</li>
        <li>Handle the API responses and integrate the data into your application.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">API Endpoints</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">The following are the main endpoints provided by JSProdigy API:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-8 mb-8">
        <li><code>GET /</code> - Retrieve the home page.</li>
        <li><code>GET /users</code> - Get a greeting message.</li>
        <li><code>POST /users/profile</code> - Create a new user profile.</li>
        <li><code>GET /users/:uid</code> - Retrieve a user profile by UID.</li>
        <li><code>POST /users/:uid</code> - Verify a user's token.</li>
        <li><code>PATCH /users/:uid</code> - Give course access to a user.</li>
        <li><code>GET /course</code> - Retrieve course information.</li>
        <li><code>GET /doubts</code> - Retrieve all doubts.</li>
        <li><code>POST /doubts</code> - Add a new doubt.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Authentication</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">JSProdigy API uses token-based authentication for certain endpoints. Include your token in the <code>Authorization</code> header of the request as follows:</p>
    <pre class="bg-gray-200 p-4 rounded mb-8"><code>Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN</code></pre>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Example Request</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">Here's an example of creating a new user profile using cURL:</p>
    <pre class="bg-gray-200 p-4 rounded mb-8"><code>curl -X POST \
 -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
 -d '{
    "uid": "user123",
    "firstName": "John",
    "lastName": "Doe",
    "email": "john@example.com",
    "phoneNumber": "1234567890",
    "dateOfBirth": "1990-01-01",
    "gender": "male",
    "occupation": "Developer",
    "educationLevel": "Bachelor's"
 }' \
 https://api.jsprodigy.com/users/profile
    </code></pre>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Error Handling</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">Most endpoints will return a 500 status code with an error message if something goes wrong on the server side. The <code>/users/:uid</code> POST endpoint will return a 401 status if the Authorization header is missing, and a 403 status if the token is invalid or doesn't match the requested UID.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Notes</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-8 mb-8">
        <li>All input is sanitized using XSS protection.</li>
        <li>Make sure to include the appropriate headers, especially the Authorization header where required.</li>
        <li>The API uses JSON for request and response bodies.</li>
    </ul>

